e financial transactions, education, the workplace, sports, electoral participation, Christmas greetings, proselytizing, and the legitimacy of choosing to live in a non-Muslim country. Shifting the focus from the authors and texts of fatwas to their recipients, Shariʿa and Life gives voice to those often left voiceless and demonstrates the great discretion and flexibility with which tensions between shariʿa and life are resolved.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aConflict of laws (Islamic law)zEurope. 0aFatwaszEurope. 0aIslamic lawzEuropexInterpretation and construction. 0aMuftis (Muslim officials)zEurope. 0aMuslimsxReligious lifezEurope. 0aReligious lifexIslam. 7aRELIGION / Islam / Shi'a.2bisacsh  aFiqh al-aqalliyyat al-Muslima.  aIslamic law.  aIslamism.  aMuslim minorities in the west.  aMuslims in Europe.  aSalafism.  aWasatiyya.  amigration.  amosque.  aradicalization.  asharia law.  ashariʿa.  asociology of law.1 aSpengler, Fabian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079736740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148755575740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487555757423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487555757/original  a978-3-11-079736-7  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles